         as said, it is an improvment but not enough.</P><P>lets assume all the necro's present on a raid are casting just 3 DoTs (assuming DoT stacking is added).  Pyre, Pyro, and Splurt.</P><P>lets also assume at the last, 5 of those slots are going to debuffs.  so that brings us to 25 slots.  lets round down to 24 just to make it easy.  we now can have 8 necro's all casting those 3, which is a nice improvment...unless of course, the shaman present also want in on the DoTs...and perhaps the druids as well.</P><P>personally, i'm going to talk to my guild (actually we have a discussion up already) and ask that necro's get priority on DoT slots, and then other classes.  shaman and druids especially have DD's that are more then suffecient....as long as that is the case, necro's on a raid should get first call on slots.</P><P>oh and just as a side note, i think that putting lifebane on poison sucks...i could be recalling wrong, but i could've sworn landing poison on most ubers (especially luclin who seem to shrug off poison/disease) is a bitch.</P><P><marquee><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/" target="_blank"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu</marquee><BR><marquee>Inverse Logic</marquee></a><BR><marquee> I'm BACK! All bow before The Scrolling Link!</marquee><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
